When a user clicks on the manage tab from the Payments Landing page they are presented with a read-only information
regarding their limits, a list of the first 5 active recipients on their recipient list by alphabetical order, and options to manage
The first card of the manage tab users can see read-only information regarding their maximum daily limit and
maximum limit per transaction. The company limit is set by the DBank employee and can only be managed on EBC
on this release. The user is also able to monitor their daily limit used and daily limit remaining on this card to ensure
they do not exceed their OU limit.
The information populated on this table is adjusted in real time as users send payments each day.
The user is able to reload the most current information by clicking on the reload icon next to the date/time stamp at
the top of the page. This will be a global reload that affects the limits card and a the recipient card (and the last
payments made to the recipients shown here). As the cards reload the date and time will also be updated to the time
From here a user can view first 5 active recipients (ordered alphabetical) and the date of the last payment made to
the recipient. A user can click on each recipient line item to access their Recipient Details page. From there they are
able to edit, delete, suspend, make a payment, and view all recipient information (see file
Users are also able to click the ‘Manage all' CTA in the card header to access the Recipient List overlay. From there
a user is able to view all of their recipients (see file DBank_RecipientManagement_DD for more details).
From the 'Manage Notifications and Alerts' card users are able to quickly view their current notification settings.
Users can easily edit their current notification settings using the 'Edit’ text link in the header row of the card.
